description:
A TOWN HALL BY THE WASHINGTON COUNTY DEMOCRATIC PARTY TO LEARN ABOUT LOCAL ORGANIZATIONS MAKING AN IMPACT IN OUR COMMUNITIES

Come learn about...
## Ride JC

Founded in 2023, Ride JC works with our communities to encourage options in how we get around for working, shopping, and playing. We are situated in the Appalachian Highlands and focus on Johnson City, Kingsport, Bristol, Greeneville, and other communities in the area. We understand that options in multimodal transportation allow people to travel the region while reducing congestion, improving the environment, and helping our health.

We use three pillars to organize our work: Community, Education, and Policy. We work to build communities for all people through events like group rides, park days, and bike clinics. Education through discussions, classes, and publications is used to inform about the benefits of different transportation methods. Finally, we work with governments through policy to provide infrastructure and ordinances that support every person in their efforts to travel.

Ride JC is committed to helping people choose how they bike, walk, or roll their communities. Join us in helping the Appalachian Highlands become more connected, sustainable, and vibrant for all people.

title: Sign-up For Democracy Action Network / Indivisible LA
description:
The Democracy Action Network (DAN) was founded in November 2024 by David Comfort in response to the re-election of Donald Trump. Emerging as a grassroots organization dedicated to defending democratic institutions, promoting civic engagement, and fostering inclusive democracy, DAN has quickly become a prominent force in the pro-democracy movement. With a nonpartisan ethos and a commitment to nonviolent resistance, DAN seeks to address threats to constitutional governance while building a broad-based coalition for democratic renewal.

Mission and Vision
DAN’s mission is to protect and strengthen democratic institutions, resist authoritarian tendencies, and promote an inclusive vision of democracy that upholds universal human rights and dignity. The organization operates on the principles of nonviolence, transparency, and participatory decision-making while fostering hope-centered messaging and constructive solutions. It aims to create sustainable organizing structures that empower communities and build long-term resilience against democratic backsliding.

Early Achievements
Since its inception, DAN has demonstrated its capacity for impactful action:

- February 22nd 2025: Organized a successful march and rally in West Hollywood, drawing hundreds of participants advocating for government accountability and democratic principles
.
- February 2025: Played a key role in coordinating protests at SpaceX, bringing attention to issues tied to corporate influence and public policy.

- Held weekly organizing meetings with 300 to 400 people attending.
- Developing a core group of activists and organizers

- March 22nd 2025: Held a really successful "March for our Constitution" at the Federal Building in Westwood / Los Angeles. Had over 2,000 participants and hosted speakers such as Martin Sheen and Maxine Waters


These events have helped establish DAN as a credible voice for democratic activism while galvanizing public support for its mission.

description:
Care in Action Arizona focuses on the #CareWins campaign represents the families, caregivers, care workers, and voters who understand that a care agenda – paid leave, childcare and pre-K, aging and disability care, and good jobs and wages for those providing care – is how we ensure we’re all able to live with the dignity and respect we deserve. Each participant will be in a cohort that corresponds for their age group (high school, collegiate, young adult) and will spend the duration of the program with their peers. Additionally, the program will be implemented through virtual learning, facilitating voter registration, and Lobby Days with the purpose of empowering communities to participate in direct action and creating a pipeline to community organizing for domestic and care workers in Arizona.

title: Rise for Freedom Training
description:
**Join the Rise for Freedom Coalition for a series of live online trainings intended for in-person groups nationwide for 6-8 weeks.** The goal of the training series is to bring people together, grow & strengthen their local networks, and get ready to mobilize to demand democracy in this new challenging environment.

*   Training content will be presented live and breakouts will take place in-person in people’s living rooms and other activist organized spaces. 
    
*   Follow up asks deemed the most important to the moment will be shared at the end of trainings as appropriate.
    
*   Training is a flexible tool that can help build for specific events as well as build existing and new local groups of people who can take action together.
    

#### **Why Trainings?**

Trainings are critical for our movement because they:

*   **Engage and recruit** more people into the freedom and democracy movement
    
*   **Educate** and onboard new activists
    
*   **Energize** large numbers of people for mobilizing and create space for local organizing and planning
    
*   **Elevate:** train higher skill activists and new and younger movement  leadership
    

**Who is Rise for Democracy For?**

This training is for people who love our country and understand the threat of autocracy before us, and want to do something about it. If you're moderate politically - this is your place! You are welcome and important here. If you're a pro-democracy conservative - this is your place! You are welcome and important in these trainings. If you’re progressive, this training is for you. 

#### **All Trainings Will Include:**

*   Music
    
*   An icebreaker
    
*   Asks for local leaders to help you prepare for action
    
*   Outreach mini training and goal setting (e.g. text 5 ppl and get 1 commit to come to your next meeting, recruit one neighbor to attend etc)
    
*   One digital hygiene tip 
    
*   One core 1.5- 2 hour training module
    
*   Breakouts for in-person and online for folks who are alone, to plan and participate in activities
    

Training calls will _not_ include lengthy one way communications about the ongoing attacks on democracy and communities. That’s a space other orgs and collaboratives we believe can and will fill.

#### **Rise for Freedom Training Timeline**

*   **Thurs. March 27 – First In-Person Meetings & Onboarding for New Folks:** Program Orientation & Context Setting, Outreach & Digital Hygiene
    
*   **Thurs. April 3 –** How did we get here? Intro to organizing under creeping autocracy
    
*   **Thurs. April 10 –** Building to a critical mass locally (outreach)
    
*   **Thurs. April 17 –** How to Talk to People You Might Disagree With
    
*   **Thurs. April 24 –** Harnessing Our Power to End Political Violence and Repression

title: Lancaster City Election Day Poll Greeting
description:
Election Day poll greeting involves volunteers stationed outside polling places to welcome voters, provide sample ballots, and offer any needed assistance or information. This friendly presence ensures that voters feel supported and informed as they exercise their right to vote.

**In local elections, where outcomes can hinge on a small number of votes, the role of poll greeters is crucial in maximizing voter turnout and ensuring a smooth voting experience.**

**Never poll greeted before?** Don't worry, we'll provide training!

### Why is Poll Greeting Important?

1. **Voter Assistance**: Poll greeters can answer last-minute questions, direct voters to the correct polling locations, and provide information on voting procedures, reducing confusion and wait times.
1. **Encouragement**: A warm welcome can boost voter morale and reinforce the importance of their participation in the democratic process.
1. **Education**: Poll greeters help ensure voters are informed about their choices before entering the polling place by distributing sample ballots and information about candidates or issues.

### Frequently Asked Questions

**What exactly is Poll Greeting?** Poll Greeters are the friendly faces you see outside your polling place who distribute sample ballots and answer questions.

**What do I need to bring?** We recommend wearing comfortable shoes and weather appropriate clothing, and bringing a charged phone to help look up information for voters if they have questions. Optionally, you can bring a chair, table, or pop-up tent; a speaker to play appropriate music (be weary you don't play music too loudly); and snacks to hand out to voters.

**What is provided to Poll Greeters?** We'll provide all of the materials and signs you need. Additionally, we provide each shift food and water.
